description:
File: firmware/bridge-zephyr/src/main.c:98-141

When standalone LoRa mode fails (CONFIG_LICHEN_LORA_L2 && !CONFIG_LICHEN_L2), the code does:
  goto main_loop;

But main_loop label is after variable declarations (lines 123-125):
  uint8_t iid[8];
  struct in6_addr ll_addr;
  char addr_str[LICHEN_IPV6_ADDR_STR_LEN];

In C, jumping over a declaration is undefined behavior if the variable is used after the label. Currently these variables are only used before the goto, so this is technically safe but fragile.

Trigger: Add code after main_loop that uses these variables.

Bad behavior: UB - uninitialized stack variables read.

Fix: Move variable declarations before any goto targets, or restructure to avoid goto.
